{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/scp-issue-between-debian-12-bookworm-and-openwrt-22.03","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"896d25be-0e91-5f7a-a03c-965e3fa9a1ca","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/4b190/openssh-debian-openwrt.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/8ac56/openssh-debian-openwrt.webp 240w,\n/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/d3be9/openssh-debian-openwrt.webp 480w,\n/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/d00b9/openssh-debian-openwrt.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/09b79/openssh-debian-openwrt.jpg 240w,\n/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/7cc5e/openssh-debian-openwrt.jpg 480w,\n/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/4b190/openssh-debian-openwrt.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/4b190/openssh-debian-openwrt.jpg\"\n            alt=\"openssh-debian-openwrt\"\n            title=\"openssh-debian-openwrt\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After I upgraded my Debian 11 Bullseye system to Debian 12 Bookworm recently, I occasionally found the <strong>scp</strong> command between Debian 12 Bookworm on my PC and OpenWRT 22.03 on my router was broken. The error message is</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">ash: /usr/libexec/sftp-server: not found\nscp: Connection closed</code></pre></div>\n<p>After debugging, I found the root cause.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>the scp server side, OpenWRT 22.03 uses <em>Dropbear v2022.82</em> which only supports legacy scp protocol by default</li>\n<li>the scp client side, Debian 12 Bookworm uses <em>OpenSSH 9.2</em> which requires sftp protocol by default</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The change comes from the default OpenSSH version change of debian, Debian 11 Bullseye uses <em>OpenSSH 8.4</em> but Debian 12 Bookworm uses <em>OpenSSH 9.2</em>. Due to the release note of <a href=\"https://www.openssh.com/txt/release-9.0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">openssh 9.0</a>. Since <em>OpenSSH 9.0</em>, OpenSSH switches scp from using the legacy scp/rcp protocol to using the sftp protocol by default.</p>\n<p>The solution is quite simple. We have two choices,</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>By following the <a href=\"https://man.openbsd.org/scp.1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">man page of scp</a>, we can add the “-O” option to force using the legacy scp protocol on the client side to avoid this error, like</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">scp</span> -O source_user@source_machine:source_path destination_user@destination_machine:destination_path</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Another choice is to install sftp server on the server side, to enable the sftp protocol support</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">opkg update\nopkg <span class=\"token function\">install</span> openssh-sftp-server</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ol>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/scp-issue-between-debian-12-bookworm-and-openwrt-22.03","tagSlugs":["/tag/linux-system/","/tag/shell/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2023-11-12T12:00:00.000Z","description":"the root cause and resolution of the scp error between Debian 12 Bookworm and OpenWRT 22.03.","tags":["Linux System","Shell"],"title":"SCP Issue between Debian 12 Bookworm and OpenWRT 22.03","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/9f244d33ecd52a91b2e8d6f83aea9d4e/openssh-debian-openwrt.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/scp-issue-between-debian-12-bookworm-and-openwrt-22.03"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}